    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nInside a normal function it is possible to automatically infer the type from an assignment.\r\ne.g.\r\n```python\r\ncdef inline test():\r\n    for j in range(<Py_ssize_t>5):\r\n        a = 10\r\n```\r\ninfers the type long for a and Py_ssize_t for j. However inside prange the following code is required\r\n```python\r\ncdef inline test():\r\n    cdef Py_ssize_t j\r\n    cdef long a\r\n    for j in prange(<Py_ssize_t>5, nogil=True):\r\n        a = 10\r\n```\r\nWithout the explicit cdef for j and a it uses the type `object` for both of them. This fails to build, since it uses nogil.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nThe types should be inferred in prange as well\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - Cython version master version #f29ef5b50736ecc03f62faf91f428a889c61e1ef\r\n",
